line_1: I lov'd thee, more; nor like a courtier, spurn'd
line_2: My benefactor, when the tide was turn'd.

line_1: With chains dishonour'd, and by eunuchs spurn'd,
line_2: Here pale and trembling, in the dust o'erturn'd,

line_1: With silver hoofs the flowery meadows spurn'd,
line_2: Roll'd his red eye, his threatening antlers turn'd.
